### Yeehaw Junction, Florida: A Census-Designated Place Where the Dust Settles and the Stories Fade

Yeehaw Junction. The very name conjures images of tumbleweeds and questionable life choices, doesn't it? It’s a [census-designated place](/Census-designated_place), which, if you ask me, is just a polite way of saying it's a place that exists on paper but might struggle to convince you in person. Located in [Osceola County, Florida](/Osceola_County,_Florida), it’s part of that sprawling, ever-expanding [Orlando](/Orlando,_Florida)&#8211;[Kissimmee](/Kissimmee,_Florida) [Metropolitan Statistical Area](/Greater_Orlando). Apparently, there was even talk of a development called [Destiny](/Destiny,_Florida) nearby. Destiny. How ironic.

